Android Development Projects using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Overview:
This repository contains a collection of Android development projects that have been built using web technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The projects included are a Stopwatch, a Tic-Tac-Toe Game, and a To-Do List. Each of these applications demonstrates the capability of building functional Android apps using web-based languages.


Projects
1. Stopwatch
A simple and precise stopwatch application. The stopwatch allows users to start, stop, and reset the timer with ease. It was developed using:
HTML: Structure of the app
CSS: Styling and layout
JavaScript: Timer logic, event handling




